Do you have a passion for creating design across the current and emerging digital landscape? Boston based, CTP, is looking to hire a Digital Product Designer who will work hand in hand with digital leads, developers and producers to create continually stronger and strategically on-target work. They would be responsible for the development and execution of creative concepts for leading edge digital marketing and web solutions. Requires a deep understanding of user-centered research, interactive development and content strategy with core strengths in user experience and communication design.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities:
Creative Management:
Conceive, develop and manage an exceptional digital creative product;
Build strong, flexible relationships with internal teams; establish credibility and win confidence of colleagues;
Generate innovative ideas across all existing and emerging platforms;
Demonstrate your ability to articulate your point of view on strategic and creative initiatives;
Apply brand systems, typography, photography, color and other elements appropriately to create innovative, leading edge digital solutions that meet user and client needs;
Understand how to break out brand stories, whether in a single product across multiple devices, or across multiple points of contact in a user’s digital ecosystem;
Extend existing visual systems/brand guidelines across all mediums with moderate design changes or interpretation;
Embrace changing web standards and principles, and be able to communicate and integrate them within the team;
Solid understanding of web development processes including: Information Architecture/Site mapping, wireframing, UX, UI, structure and interaction prototyping, developer handoff, and quality assurance testing;
An understanding of design patterns and how design decisions have an impact on the implementation in HTML, CSS & JavaScript using web standards;
Understanding of motion design and the strengths and limitations of HTML5, Javascript, CSS3.
Leadership and Communication:
Share your passions for and knowledge of technology and digital marketing;
Demonstrate a clear, comfortable, persuasive presentation style in both formal and informal settings;
Exude strong problem-solving ability and showcase the ability to be flexible and adaptable;
Guide, teach and mentor junior members of the creative department in developing ideas further;
Communicate effectively in both a verbal and written manner;
Maintain the level of creative standards at CTP.
CTP is a Boston-based digital, advertising and PR agency based in Boston’s historic North End that turns data-driven insights into award-winning work and measurable results for our clients. Today's consumers demand authentic engagement. Speaking to their interests. Listening to their desires. Responding to their worries. Understanding their emotions. Our people have that rare and oh-so-human ability to craft those conversations and tap into the human spirit.
CTP offers great benefits and is committed to a rewarding work/life balance for all employees.

## Duties and Responsibilities

The Senior Web Developer plays 3 important roles:

- Building wireframes to visualize UED ideas, and implementing POC or prototypes alike;

- Designing, developing, and delivering robust web applications with high maintainability and extensibility;

- Solving complex problems using a variety of web techniques where needed;
## Desired Skills and Experience

The Senior Web Developer is a senior-level position for applicants with who are creative, innovative, and passionate for building advanced financial research products with best-in-class solutions. We seek self-driven seasoned professionals with a strong, versatile background in application development, a deep knowledge of modern web standards and techniques, and a desire for solving problems elegantly.

Candidates should have the following qualifications:


Strong hands-on experience of

- web languages including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript;

- web frameworks such as Angular, Vue.js, Bootstrap, LESS, Semantic UI, etc;

- web tools like Git, NPM, Webpack, Yarn, Grunt, Bower, etc.;

- web libraries including jQuery, underscore.js, and/or Lodash;

- server-side web techniques like Node.js, Express, etc;
Advanced knowledge of

- web standards and web browsers quirks;

- web performance analysis and optimization;
Advanced ability to

- work independently and solve problems elegantly

- communicate effectively with counterparts and managers
A bachelor's degree with 5 years of experience or a master's degree with 3 years of experience.
